 <text>
  <front>
   <head>BARLEY BROTH.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">IF tempers were put up to seale,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Our Jwohn's wad bear a duced preyce;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">He vow'd 'twas barley i' the broth, —</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Upon my word, says I, it's reyce.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">"I mek nea faut," our Jwohnny says,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">"The broth is guid and varra neyce;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I only say — it's barley broth."</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Tou says what's wrang, says I, it's reyce.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Did ever mortal hear the leyke!</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">As if I hadn't sense to tell!</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Tou may think reyce the better thing,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But barley broth dis just as well. "</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">"And sae it mud, if it was there;</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The deil a grain is i' the pot;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But tou mun ayways threep yen down, —</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I've drawn the deevil of a lot!"</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">"And what's the lot that I have drawn?</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Pervarsion is a woman's neame!</l>
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Sae fares-te-weel! I'll sarve my king,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And never, never mair come heame."</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="6" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Now Jenny frets frae mworn to neet;</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">The Sunday cap's nae langer neyce;</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">She aye puts barley i' the broth,</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And hates the varra neame o' reyce.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="7" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="25" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thus treyfles vex, and treyfles please,</l>
     <l n="26" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And treyfles mek the sum o' leyfe;</l>
     <l n="27" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And treyfles mek a bonny lass</l>
     <l n="28" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A wretched or a happy weyfe!</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
